<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n22063j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n22" href="#n22063j">N22 (VI.B.17)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n22all.htm#n22063j"> 63(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> beautybelt</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Manus has &ldquo;costly coloured belts on his left side, with which might be won the love of a young woman, and the liking of maidens.&rdquo; &mdash; This feature is probably derived from the beauty-belt of Venus. <small> Alexander Bugge, <a name="ABUG" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ABUG"><cite title="source">Contributions to the History of the Norsemen in Ireland</cite></a> (1900) II, 12</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
